# Environment Variables

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in your Jira credentials:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

## Required Variables

```
JIRA_BASE_URL=https://your-jira-instance.com
JIRA_USERNAME=your-username
JIRA_PASSWORD=your-password
```

## Optional Variables - HTTP Server Configuration

```
# MCP HTTP Server Configuration
MCP_HOST=127.0.0.1  # HTTP server host (default: 127.0.0.1)
MCP_PORT=3000       # HTTP server port (default: 3000)

# Jira API Configuration
JIRA_API_VERSION=2  # API version (default: 2)
```

## MCP Endpoint

The server exposes a single MCP endpoint at:
`http://<MCP_HOST>:<MCP_PORT>/mcp`

This endpoint supports:
- POST requests for tool calls and other MCP operations
- GET requests for SSE streaming (when enabled)
